reviews.review: I absolutely loved it. Was it absolute perfection, probably not, but I did enjoy myself. If you haven't read any of the books or anything like that, but you have seen the rest of the movies, and maybe even the cartoons, then you should enjoy it as well.

People, it's fantasy, someone else's imagination, meant for entertainment.  Not to be confused with formal human history books.  Great movie, enjoyed every minute of it.  I'd rate it 2 in the series, behind A New Hope.  Only because I saw ANH at the theater in 1977, as a 12yr old, so it has more sentimental value.....
Our whole family absolutely loved this movie.  The perfect end for an awesome series of movies that have been with us throughout our lifetime!

About the only good thing I can say about this movie is that it didn't suck as bad as Last Jedi.  But the plot is pretty stupid.  The characters are thin and do things that don't make sense.  The movie was mildly entertaining but at no point was I on the edge of my seat.  Unfortunately it just ends up being another Star Wars movie that I don't think I will ever watch again.
Way over the top, way too far fetched,  they invent stuff that never happens.  Im done with star wars.
JJ does for Star Wars what Michael Bay did for Transformers. A big, dumb, loud mess of a movie. But if you know that going in, there's some fun to be had.
Great continuation of series with a lot of great surprises!
Loved the knods to previous movies and the Cameo performances by Han Solo and Luke Skywalker.

Easily the best of Episodes 7-9.  There are certainly some moments where I would have liked to see something different but the movie delivers a solid wrap to the Skywalker Saga which is not an easy thing to do.  Plenty of light-hearted moments that come with Star Wars mixed with drama and plenty of action.  Great lightsaber battles which is always a key.  Really enjoyed the film and our whole family (me + wife and kids aged 4, 7 & 9) enjoyed it as well.
